pageContext.claim: “I withdrew the United States from the horrible one-sided Iran nuclear deal. And Iran is a much different country. They're trying to put out all the riots they have all over that country.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump exaggerates the unrest in Iran since he withdrew the U.S. from the Iran nuclear deal. "The protests over the past six months have been relatively isolated, sporadic, scattered and much smaller than the anti government demonstrations in 2009, when millions took to the streets," the New York Times reported in August.
